diff:1619317645:1619317645:=1,45d0%0a%3c :Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a%3c :Expansion: Usage of “fixin’ to” in Texas%0a%3c :Author: albert_l%0a%3c :Original: [[Articles.StevenCrowderDiscriminatingAgainstAAVE|StevenCrowderDiscriminatingAgainstAAVE]] %0a%3c :OriginalAuthor: [[Profiles.JacobF|JacobF]]%0a%3c :Section: A%0a%3c :Completed: 24.04.2021 - 19:27%0a%3c :Status: ungraded%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeExpansion:)%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#history]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#historyend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c %25red%25 '''Comments to student'''%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#comments]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#commentsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c !!%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c [[#content]]%0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.texasstandard.org/stories/the-case-for-fixin-to-as-the-official-verb-of-texas/%0a%3c %0a%3c I found an interesting story in the Texas Standard, where W.F. Strong, a Fullbright scholar and professor of Culture and Communication at the University of Texas Rio Grande Valley, provides his personal experience with the verb “fixin’ to” as a native resident of Texas, and offers an interesting grammatical perspective on the usage of the verb.%0a%3c %0a%3c One aspect of the verb “fixin’ to” that W.F. Strong highlights is the malleability of the verb, as well as its ability to be used in various situations. He defines these as “Intentionality”, “Contemplation”, and “Forewarning”, and provides a comedic example of the verb used multiple times in the same sentence: “I was fixin’ to fix it this mornin’, but I decided to fix breakfast first cuz I saw all these fixins which I knew would make a fine omelette. So right now I’m fixin’ to eat, but when I finish I’m fixin to look for my tools –if I can find ‘em – and get started on fixin’ your mower.” W.F. Strong also provides an interesting regional variation of “fixin’ to”, where the final “o” is replaced with “a” leaving the meaning unchanged. %0a%3c %0a%3c I think it is interesting to note that not only are certain phrases and words regionally diverse across the language speaking population, but also contain regional variations in usage and expression which improve upon its diversity. %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:Category:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
